 in the tasks of designing real objects or technological processes should reflect the real physical and, as a rule, nonlinear processes occurring in them. The variables of these objects or processes are interconnected by physical non-linear laws, such as the laws of conservation of mass or energy. They are limited to the limiting ranges that ensure the physical realizability of a given object or process. As a result, most of the tasks of mathematical programming that occur in research projects and in design problems are non-linear programming (NP) problems. \"','1',false,false,false,false)
