 методы решения линейных краевых задач и их компьютерная реализация.','Most application problems lead to differential equations. They, as a rule, arise in various branches of natural science as mathematical models of the process under study. Therefore, the ability of undergraduates to investigate the solvability of boundary value problems for differential equations, as well as master the skills of computer implementation of numerical methods, is important. The special course deals with linear boundary value problems for differential equations. The basic concepts of the theory of linear ordinary differential equations and boundary value problems are introduced. We study the basic methods used in the study and solution of linear boundary value problems. Numerical and approximate methods for solving linear boundary value problems and their computer implementation.','1',false,false,false,false)
		");

