uted computing models and algorithms. The course program covers the mathematical principles of the organization and architecture of the functioning of modern computing systems, including multiprocessor and multi-core; structures and functions of modern operating systems, conventional and distributed; scheduling algorithms, memory management, interaction and synchronization of processes, knowledge and data bases, grammar, technology and parallel programming languages.','6',false,false,false,false)
