алгоритмов, эволюционного программирования, ассоциативной памяти, нечеткой логики.','This course describes the basics of data analysis methods such as classification, modeling and forecasting methods based on the use of decision trees, artificial neural networks, genetic algorithms, evolutionary programming, associative memory, fuzzy logic. Students will learn data analysis methods, including statistical methods: descriptive analysis, correlation and regression analysis, factor analysis, analysis of variance, component analysis, discriminant analysis, time series analysis, survival analysis, link analysis. This will help them to get some a priori understanding of the data being analyzed. One of the most important goals of data analysis methods is visualization of calculation results (visualization). The complexity and diversity of data mining methods require the creation of specialized end-user tools for solving typical information analysis tasks in specific areas. Since these tools are used in complex multi-functional decision support systems, they should be easily integrated into such systems. Intelligent data analysis systems are used in research, education, law enforcement, manufacturing, healthcare, and many other areas. In particular, data mining technology is used in business applications.','6',false,false,false,false)
